title: For Sale:  adam arms 545x39 piston upper
postcontent:
This Adams Arms AR-15 A3 Base Carbine Gas Piston Upper Assembly is chambered for the cheap and plentiful 5.45x39mm round, and comes ready to fire right out of the box after installation onto any standard AR-15 lower receiver. This Base Carbine upper comes equipped with a 16" melonite-finished barrel, A2 flash hider, ion-bonded bolt carrier group, charging handle assembly, picatinny rail gas block, 30-round magazine, delta ring assembly and a set of polymer M4-style handguards. Additional features include a forged A3 flat-top configuration that's ready to accept the shooter's choice of optic and/or rear iron sight, M4 feed ramps to help ensure reliable feeding and functioning during rapid strings of fire, and a carbine length gas system. Also includes a Wolff extra power hammer spring to ensure proper ignition of foreign military surplus ammunition with hard primers. 

The upper's barrel has been finished inside and out with Adams Arms' proprietary QPQ Melonite treatment that bonds with the metal on a molecular level. Also referred to as salt bath nitriding, this treatment produces an extremely hard, slick surface on steel that resists carbon adhesion and increases corrosion resistance, extending a barrel's service life by reducing the friction produced inside the bore upon firing for a net decrease in bore surface wear over time. Nitriding converts the barrel steel's surface without any build-up, retaining all of the benefits of traditional chrome lining without suffering the accuracy degradation commonly encountered due to uneven application of chrome inside the barrel's bore. The end result is a barrel that's capable of producing accuracy on par with a match stainless steel tube, while also exhibiting the longevity and resilience of a chrome lined, mil-spec barrel. The QPQ Melonite finish protecting the barrel, piston components and flash hider is so corrosion resistant and durable that it is not adversely affected by prolonged exposure to the corrosive primer residue that's often left behind after firing military surplus 5.45x39mm ammo. While immediate cleaning of all steel parts after shooting corrosive ammunition is still recommended, it is not necessary. 

All Adams Arms uppers feature a short stroke gas piston operating system, which prevents hot gas and debris from being directed back into the action upon firing. The result is a rifle that runs cooler, cleaner and more reliably than those utilizing a standard direct gas impingement system of operation. To ensure that damage doesn't occur to the buffer tube from carrier tilt, the bolt carrier is equipped with enlarged "skis" to help guide it into the receiver extension. The bolt carrier's solid steel, 1-piece construction incorporates an integral piston strike face to guarantee integrity over time, while the bolt assembly is spring loaded for proper lock-up and to help reduce bolt bounce and cam pin wear. All piston components are finished in QPQ Melonite for corrosion resistance and easy cleaning/maintenance.

title: For Sale/Trade:  1/2 MOA accurate DMR style AR
postcontent:
DMR style AR with a 16" SS barrel built on a brand new billet lower. Trigger is brand new and breaks at a clean 4 pounds. Magpul Furniture. Free float tube. 

Actual round count on this matched barrel/bolt is probably under 300 rounds. The gun has ALWAYS been stored in a climate controlled area.

The barrel is a match chambered SS 9 twist barrel with a carbine length gas system for reliability. Has a forward assist and dust cover. The barrel sits inside a brand new knurled free float tube. It has a charging handle with a steel extended handle to clear optics when charging the rifle. The SS barrel has been painted. A 9 twist barrel will easily stabilize anything up to 75 grains. 

The barrel is extremely accurate. The group in the pictures below was last time this barrel was shot. It has proven to be extremely accurate with several different bullet weights. That is a .372" CTC group at 100 yards, how many AR's do you know that can do that?

Since that group was shot I installed a brand new free float tube as well as installed the upper on a brand new Valley Ordinance Works billet lower with all brand new internal parts. The lower was assembled as a pistol first and I can write a affidavit declaring such as well as provide a picture as proof it was.

The trigger was professionally done, breaks cleanly at 4 pounds and is 100% reliable. It has a Magpul rifle stock with a QD point and plenty of storage in the back. It has a heavy buffer carbine buffer to ensure reliability with a spacer installed to be able to use a rifle length buffer tube. By using a carbine buffer means you can swap out various buffer weights and not be stuck with a single weight like when you have a rifle buffer. It has a marksman style pistol grip that is adjustable for hand size. All parts on this billet lower are brand new.

The upper receiver was squared to ensure the rifle is consistently accurate. This is the same thing that is done by all the high end AR builders when ultimate accuracy is the priority. Here are pictures of the process.
http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v446/Adyth/ac265c65_zps41d385f7.jpg
http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v446/Adyth/7d7c8d15_zps84131b7a.jpg

All work was done by a professional. This is an extremely accurate rifle without the weight normally associated with ARs as accurate as this. This would be an excellent hunting rifle because it does not weigh a ton and is easily carried in the field. Would be a great gun for hunting coyotes, deer or pigs.

It has a B.E. Meyers flash hider and is considered one of the best money can buy, a $100 value.
http://www.weaponoutfitters.com/be-meyers-flash-hider-for-5-56mm-weapons-1.html
I have tested it at night and it eliminates the flash.

There are some minor marks on the upper from the scope being mounted but nothing too bad.

I will include either a 20 round Lancer magazine or a 30 round Magpul magazine.

Will take partial trade of M92 AK pistol. Will require $200 plus the M92 AK pistol. If you have the 75 round drum magazine I will only need $100 on top.

If you are in the Knoxville area I can meet you at a public range to shoot the gun.

title: For Sale:  1800's Smith Double Barrel 12 Gauge Damascus - Restored
postcontent:
This is a beauty.  If you're reading this...you're interested, so go ahead and make me an offer.  I completely restored this shotgun, from the inside out.
The Stock:  The patina from a 200-year-old piece of wood was maintained, in terms of dark stains etc.  The checkering was freshened up, all cracks repaired, sealed and coated with over 20 coats of Tru-Oil before I buffed it out with Rottenstone and applied the final stock wax!  Simply perfect, and beautiful.  Contact me for more pictures, I couldn't upload that many.

The Hardware:  All steel Hardware was rust-blued and turned out fantastic without compromising the etching.  The Locks were completely disassembled, polished, and the back side of each lock was jeweled.  

The Barrel:  The rib was completely removed as it was loose.  The resolder job is perfect, the barrel rings like a bell when you give it that test.  I then reblued the barrel using the old-school rust blue with Ferric Cloride Acid bath to etch the Damascus barrel appropriately.  

The only part of this that was not touched, was the inside of the barrels.  They do show their age, but are clean.  I didn't want to invest in the back-boring hardware to pull that job off.  

I know you'll enjoy this beauty!  I'm not a shotgun guy, but did enjoy the restoration.  Time to sell it and move on to the next project.  Contact me if you're interested.  I have many pictures both before, during and after the project was completed.

I will trade for a Henry .44 Mag. AND/OR Reloading equipment
